Text.Value: Zevlor turned to darkness in his desperation... but he did not deserve a fate such as that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sombre. Referring to an old acquaintance who was found dead and mutilated
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 185 - Didn't save Zevlor from the Colony, entered Wyrm's Crossing, camped

Text.Value: I have no idea.
Fair. But a decision is still needed.
A shame that Minsc had to die. I sense he could have been an ally to us, had circumstances been different.
A cruel parting of ways with Shadowheart. I can only hope the allies we have won will be worth our betrayal.
It may be some centuries before my flesh is ready to yield, but I hope I shall be bold enough to follow in her path, when the day comes.
Very well...
Astarion... he has ascended amongst the ranks of the undead. I can only hope that he does not come to regret the price that he paid.
You carry a most dire burden inside you, Gale. I wish you had shared it with us sooner.
This orb... Gale carries a most dire burden. I wish he had shared it with us sooner.
It will be me. I'll become illithid. I'm not afraid.
Our work is not yet finished - not until Ketheric Thorm's last breath flees his corpse. Let us pursue him.
Vampire spawn assailing us in the night? I thought we had ample troubles as it was. At least you are safe, Astarion.
Vampire spawn assailing us in the night? I thought we had ample troubles as it was. At least Astarion is safe.
Orin has made off with Gale - we must rescue him... unless you wish to kill Gortash for her.
What are you thinking?
What are you thinking?
Moonrise Towers. Many druids and Harpers died to take this place once... only for Ketheric Thorm to rule it once again.
This place is not of the natural realm... it is the domain of darkness, emptiness, sheer nothingness.
A temple dedicated to Shar. More than a temple perhaps - a proving ground. This must be where Ketheric Thorm grew his dark-cloaked ranks.
The belly of the city. How many people are born, live, and die within these walls without ever seeing the depths of nature's beauty for themselves? I shudder to think.
Lorroakan hunts powerful game - too powerful for him, perhaps. Dame Aylin should be informed that yet another ambitious fool lusts after her.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 155 - Lorroakan states his intention to retrieve Nightsong

Text.Value: There is something foul to to air here - it reeks of madness and death.
Orin has taken Yenna. We must free her - either by force, or by paying for her freedom with Gortash's life.
Fair. But a decision is still needed.
You have carried this burden for too long already - I simply do not believe that ceremorphosis is the only course left to you. Orpheus must help us.
You were wise to turn from Shar, Shadowheart. Now your family is restored, and the healing can begin.
Shar sought rob Shadowheart of her family - of her true nature. But no more. Now the  healing can begin.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 164 - Enemy of Shar SH freed parents

Text.Value: Gale defied Mystra herself. I hope he does not come to regret it.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 182 - COM Gale met Mystra - defied

Text.Value: You resisted the allure of Cazador's would-be powers? I am glad. Whatever there was to gain would have come at a great price.
Astarion resisted the allure of Cazador's would-be powers - and I am glad of it. Whatever he would have gained would have come at a great price.
Jaheira's family is a credit to her - she is wise to keep them secret, safe.
Gale, you truly thought to turn to shadow magic, after seeing how it has ravaged nature? Your ambitions are... disquieting.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 175 - Gale has crafted the Dark Lantern

Text.Value: I trust you to do what you think is best... but I just hope that we can indeed trust the Emperor in turn...
I was never afforded a chance to start a family of my own - serving nature always had to come first.
Karlach has had her mortality defined to her in most cruel terms... I do not know if we can help her, but perhaps we can at least be there for her.
A city within a city, older as you go deeper. Much like the rings of a tree.

EditorData.NodeContext: Commenting on extensive ruins beneath a city

Text.Value: A hammer capable of shattering the bonds in the Astral Plane? That sounds like something we should seek out.
We have the hammer - now is the time to use it. We'll release Orpheus.
Those vampire spawn made off with Astarion. It shall fall to us to rescue him.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 143 - Vampire spawn attack/Astarion taken away

Text.Value: You faced the scorn of a goddess, and still draw breath. That is an uncommon feat, Shadowheart.
Shar's ire has shaken Shadowheart... and yet she goes on. There is untold strength there, I feel.
I am unsure if Shadowheart would have remained committed to the darkness, if put to the test... but we did not afford her the chance to decide.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 158 - SH left party post-Shar Temple

Text.Value: Astarion... you have ascended amongst the ranks of the undead. I can only hope that you do not come to regret the price that you paid.
Astarion... he has ascended amongst the ranks of the undead. I can only hope that he does not come to regret the price that he paid.
Mystra has forsaken Gale entirely. A crushing blow... but he is strong enough to persevere, I think.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 181 - COM Gale met Mystra - failed to earn forgiveness

Text.Value: Shadowheart... fulfilling your parents' wishes took courage beyond measure. I hope true peace finds its way to you swiftly.
A cruel task fell to Shadowheart... but she did as her parents wished. She has my eternal respect, and I hope she soon finds peace.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 166 - Enemy of Shar SH killed parents

Text.Value: To defy a goddess is no small thing, Shadowheart. Perhaps the darkness is not your true nature.
It is no small thing, to defy a goddess. Perhaps the darkness is not Shadowheart's true nature.
Nature cares little for nobility - it is pure artifice - but I can still respect your achievement, Wyll. You shall be a fine Duke, I am sure.
Nature cares little for nobility - it is pure artifice - but I can still hold some respect for Wyll's accomplishment. He shall be a fine Duke, I am sure.
So, you've committed to being the Blade of Frontiers. None can doubt you've earned the title. Well done.
It seems that Wyll's determined to remain the Blade of Frontiers. I suppose he's truly earned the moniker, now.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 134 - Wyll Blade of Frontiers Decision

Text.Value: Your loyalty stands to you, Lae'zel. I can only hope Vlaakith recognises it as I do.
Lae'zel's faith in her queen is unshakeable, it seems. I just hope Vlaakith recognises that.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 139 - Voss Camp/Lae'zel loyal to Vlaakith

Text.Value: Your self-discipline has been rewarded, I think. Perhaps Mystra is more invested in your survival than you might believe...

EditorData.NodeContext: Thoughtful. Reacting to Avatar Gale seemingly gaining a blessing for ressiting the urge to consume dark magic.

Text.Value: Once, you would have to sway hearts in order to raise an army... but with this place? Any tyrant could lay claim to legions of artificial killers.
Karlach... I am sorry. I shall not try to soothe you with gilded words, but know that I am here for you.
Karlach has had her mortality defined to her in most cruel terms... I do not know if we can help her, but perhaps we can at least be there for her.
Minsc believes a doppelganger to be Jaheira? He is being manipulated - I am all but certain.
Minsc has great heart - we shall need the likes of him, for the trials to come.
I cannot imagine how you are feeling, Gale. For a goddess to ask a mortal to pay such a price. I am sorry for, for your burden... though I wish you had told us of your predicament before.
Mizora dead... and Wyll, doomed to the Hells. Oak Father, lend him your strength.
We allowed Astarion to sacrifice so many, only to just turn on him soon after? We should have stopped him sooner.
I cannot imagine how you are feeling, Gale. For a goddess to ask a mortal to pay such a price... I am sorry for, for your burden.
This place is unnatural in ways I cannot truly fathom - a vile celebration of death without purpose.
For that at least, I am thankful.
I can only hope he manages to find what he needs - for his sake and ours.
That... creature you changed into. I pray to Silvanus that you have it under control.
Gortash's bluster will no longer assail our ears. And we have his Netherstone also - soon we shall unravel this unnatural conspiracy, once and for all.
You sacrificed a great deal for your family, Wyll. The pact may stand, but the strength of your character is clear.
Wyll sacrificed a great deal for his family. The pact may stand, but the strength of his character is clear.
Your rage is most impressive, Karlach. If the lesson is to not provoke your temper, consider it well-learned.
Karlach's rage is like a force of nature. I pity those who bear its brunt.
Your queen's words have set your mind then, Lae'zel? I would not wish to be the one that Vlaakith unleashes you upon.
Vlaakith's words have set Lae'zel's mind, it seems. I would not wish to be the one that the Lich Queen unleashes her upon.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 142 - Vlaakith camp/Lae'zel Vlaakith path after

Text.Value: Jaheira's wisdom is plain to see. She understands that to truly serve nature, you must one day surrender your body back to it.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 157 - Jaheira Timeless Body Scroll kept

Text.Value: Mizora has something planned for you, Wyll. I could see it in her eyes... and I fear it does not bode well.
Mizora schemes with Wyll's very freedom. He deserves to know what she is up to.
Jaheira's wisdom is plain to see. One of the greatest ways in which you can serve nature, is to surrrender your body back to it, when the time comes.
Mystra would ask for Gale's life in return for forgiveness...? A cruel demand to make of a mortal.
Karlach has offered to take up the mantle. I think you should let her have her wish. Her time is short, but she can live on in all the hearts of those she will have saved.
Sacrifice Orpheus, sacrifice the githyanki people to an eternity of Vlaakith's tyranny. I will not allow it.
Shadow magic, Gale...? No matter how desperate times become, you should not defile yourself with such foul matters. You are better than that.
I fought proudly alongside Harpers once... but it seems we cannot place our trust in them now - not while Orin has their ranks infiltrated.
You are taking the fight to the very Hells themselves, Wyll? I can think of none more capable.
Wyll intends to take the fight to the very Hells themselves? I can think of no one more capable.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 135 - Wyll Blade of Avernus Decision

Text.Value: Shadowheart... you truly are Shar's instrument now. At least perhaps your dark-cloaked followers may prove of service against the Absolute.
Shadowheart truly is Shar's instrument now. At least perhaps her new dark-cloaked followers can help in the fight against the Absolute.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 167 - Shar path SH killed parents

Text.Value: So be it. Whatever happens, I shall stand by you.
A pact made with Raphael will surely bring nothing but misfortune, as much as I would like to be proven wrong.
I am sorry, Gale. You tried. Mystra was wrong to turn on you, no matter what mistakes you made in the past.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 178 - Avatar Gale met Mystra - failed to earn forgiveness

Text.Value: Will Orin truly free Lae'zel if we slay Gortash? I am not so sure... a rescue may be in order.
Alfira died badly. I can only hope the others that share this campfire do not share her fate...
It seems Gale has made amends with Mystra. I see this as a good omen for what awaits us.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 180 - COM Gale met Mystra - forgiven

Text.Value: Not a decision you have made lightly, I trust. You have my support, no matter what.
I thought your faith in Vlaakith was unshakeable, Lae'zel. Perhaps Voss will prove to be a more worthy ally.
I thought Lae'zel's faith in Vlaakith was unshakeable. Perhaps Voss shall prove to be a more worthy ally to her.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 140 - Voss Camp/Lae'zel agreed to meet him

Text.Value: It seems you have made amends with Mystra, Gale. Congratulations. I see this as a good omen for what awaits us.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 177 - Avatar Gale met Mystra - forgiven

Text.Value: Of course Thorm would flee to such a repellent, unnatural place. Let us put an end to him and get out of here.
I can already sense the first stirrings of new life in the land. The grip of the curse is weakening - now we must break it, once and for all.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hopeful/determined. His lifelong goal of cleansing a cursed land is nearly fulfilled

Text.Value: I had hoped you would shun Bhaal's overtures... but those hopes are dashed. To be a vessel for murder itself? I can think of few things less natural.
For so long, we have fought the Absolute... only to now learn you were once one of its masterminds? There is nothing we can take for granted.
The final battle is upon us. May the Oak Father grant us victory.
Shadowheart. To turn from Shar cannot have been easy... but having your family by your side shows you did what was right.
Shadowheart's true nature won out in the end, no matter how much Shar tried to bury it. It gladdens my heart to see a family reunited.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 165 - Shar path SH freed parents

Text.Value: I see... then I hope she understands. You have steered us true, thus far.
I am sorry, Gale... but Mystra is wrong about you. Perhaps you can yet prove that.
Poor Gale... but Mystra is wrong about him. Perhaps he can yet prove that.
Let us not forget that we also have the Orphic Hammer. We could free Orpheus, let him wield the stones - if we can trust him.
You made a hard choice, Wyll. But not one that is unknown in nature. At times, a seedling must strangle the very tree that bore it, if it is to survive.
Wyll sacrificed his own father... a hard choice, but not one that is unknown in nature. At times, a seedling must strangle the very tree that bore it, if it is to survive.
Astarion resisted the allure of Cazador's would-be powers - and I am glad of it. Whatever he would have gained would have come at a great price.
I spoke to Karlach already - I agreed to let her transform. This is what she wants.
Sacrifice Orpheus, sacrifice the githyanki people to an eternity of Vlaakith's tyranny. I will not allow it.
Last Light fell because you could not control the violence in your heart. All those people perished because of what you did to Isobel. You must try harder. You must be better.
Defying a goddess, Gale? And one you have known so intimately? I hope you do not come to regret this.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 179 - Avatar Gale met Mystra - defied

Text.Value: A curious discovery, this place. This city builds and builds upon itself, until it forgets its own secrets.
A lair of undeath - most unnatural. We must tread carefully.
I don't want this for Karlach; I won't allow it.
So, only a mind flayer can wield the stones, if you trust the Emperor's word. You are already part-illithid, but this is a whole other matter...
So, only a mind flayer can wield the stones, if you trust the Emperor's word.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 174 - Learned that for the Netherstone to be effective, the avatar or companion Karlach needs to be a mind flayer

Text.Value: This 'stone lord' and Minsc are one and the same? Jaheira's friend has taken a dark turn, it seems.
All of nature's creatures need to consume something to sustain themselves... but Gale needs to absorb powerful magic...?

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 102  - Companion Gale consumed Magic Item

Text.Value: Freeing Mizora... I can only hope that is a kindness we do not come to regret.
The Netherbrain's lair. We may be near the end of all this...
Shar's worshippers had ambitions beyond their strength, it seems. The Astral Prism - or its inhabitants - would never have yielded to them.
Now, the final decision rests with you. Whatever you choose, I shall be by your side.
A pity. I sensed a love of nature and animals in her. There may have been more to her than even she knew of.
I need it. You see, I have rather dangerous malady that threatens myself - and others - if I do not sate it with magical items...
How can such a predicament come to be, I wonder...?
An infernal abode. This is not a place in which we should linger too long.
None of us are about to turn into an illithid. I shall give the stones to the Emperor.
We had an item of great magic before - what came of it, Gale?

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 102  - Avatar Gale consumed Magic Item

Text.Value: So be it, then. We must do all we can to help her reach her destiny.
The battle is not yet over - yet we still stand. Let us finish this.
The depths are no place for me - I shall be glad to walk upon dry land once again.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 113 - Return from the Iron Throne

Text.Value: The Orphic Hammer is ours. Now to put it to use.
I sincerely hope that acquiring that amulet was the lesser of two evils...
Yet, she fears there are none to inherit her work, so she goes on. Long life can be a burden at times - I know that well.
I cannot believe Mystra would truly sacrifice a mind such as Gale's in order to stop the Absolute... he has so much potential...
Hidden in the depths. The perfect place for nefarious secrets.
Battle has been joined. We cannot let up until Ketheric Thorm is no more.
So, it seems that Vlaakith is your queen no longer, Lae'zel. That took no small amount of backbone.
So, it seems that Vlaakith is Lae'zel's queen no longer. That took no small amount of backbone.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 141 - Vlaakith camp/Lae'zel Orpheus path after

Text.Value: So, only a mind flayer can wield the stones, if you trust the Emperor's word. You are already part-illithid, but this is a whole other matter...
So, only a mind flayer can wield the stones, if you trust the Emperor's word.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 173 - Learned that for the Netherstone to be effective, the avatar needs to be a mind flayer

Text.Value: A foul place, that we have found ourselves in. But at least we survived the fall.
There is no deal with a devil that I would willingly partake in. Declining Raphael showed great wisdom.
Wyrm's Crossing - the gaping maw of the city. Nature has little control over what happens beyond that bridge.
Remember - whatever evil is trying to control you, I know you are stronger. Resist.
Shadowheart. These truths that have been revealed to you... I know they must be painful. But, Oak Father as my witness, I know you are strong enough to bear them. You need not walk this path alone.
Painful truths have been thrust upon Shadowheart. I believe she is strong enough to endure, but her path will be easier with our support.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 162 - SH learned of past from NS

Text.Value: Bears have perhaps the best sense of smell of all animals - a curse in a place such as this.
But let us not forget that we also have the Orphic Hammer. We could free Orpheus, let him wield the stones - if we can trust him.
Raphael is no more. I shall not shed any tears.
The decision is made. I can only pray to the Oak Father that we choose wisely. Onwards.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 112 - Orpheus Brain consumption / Turning into a mindflayer

Text.Value: Bhaal has condemned you to madness... I can only hope it does not come to pass.
A shapeshifter infiltrating our number, like a cuckoo creeping into the nest? A dire threat, if Gortash indeed spoke the truth.
Glad to have you back with us, Gale. The group would be poorer without your insights - and your company.
I am glad to have Gale back with us. The group would be poorer without his insights - and his company.
I cannot believe Mystra would truly sacrifice a mind such as Gale's in order to stop the Absolute... he has so much potential...
Even with the shadow curse gone, Shar's presence blooms everywhere. No doubt her teachings have found a strong purchase amongst the city's populace.
Astarion, you have a remarkably healthy gleam in your eye, for one arguably closer to death than life.
Astarion seems well - full of life, even. I hope that does not mean that someone else is lacking life.
Karlach. I am glad you can enjoy the touch of another once again... and I hope you are afforded much more time than you have been told. A lifetime and more, if I have a say in it.
My heart grows heavy for Karlach. She can touch, once more... yet is her remaining time to truly be so short? I shall pray to Silvanus that it does not come to pass.
An unfortunate battle... but I must stand by those I count as allies.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 151 - Defeated the Gur Hunters with Vampire Lord Astarion (Avatar only)

Text.Value: I cannot believe that Gale kept such a secret from us... and now his goddess wishes him to make the ultimate sacrifice in her name...?
The blight that was Orin has been purged from the world. And we have another Netherstone also - a significant step towards stopping this evil, once and for all.
So your confidante was a mind flayer all along...? Disquietening, to say the least...
One of us must take this step, Karlach. Your time with us is dwindling. Please, make it count.
One of us must take this step... and Karlach's time is already dwindling. Perhaps she is the champion we need.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 132 - Orpheus Decision - wants Karlach mind flayer

Text.Value: The moon weeps, Shadowheart, for what you have done. For your sake, I hope the approval of your goddess was worth it.
The moon weeps, for what Shadowheart has done. For her sake, I hope the approval of her goddess was worth it.
You fought hard to win back control over yourself. I can only imagine how you feel - congratulations.
That foul shapeshifter Orin is like a scavenger beast - probing us for weaknesses. Do not let her shake your resolve.
Shadowheart. Your tresses are... different. It suits you - though in truth, I cannot imagine much does not suit you.
I was concerned when I saw Shadowheart creeping about with a blade in the dead of night, but it was just to cut her hair, it seems. It suits her.
